{"id":"cherokee-foothills-scenic-highway","generatedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z","designation":"National Scenic Byway","parkCode":null,"source":{"roadArticle":"South Carolina Highway 11","revisionId":1349849571,"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Carolina_Highway_11"},"attribution":{"license":"CC BY-SA 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/","articleUrl":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Carolina_Highway_11","text":"Route, junction, and history details adapted from the Wikipedia article \"South Carolina Highway 11\", by Wikipedia contributors, licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0."},"sources":[{"name":"Wikipedia","src":"wikipedia","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Carolina_Highway_11","revisionId":1349849571,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"},{"name":"Federal Highway Administration — National Scenic Byways","src":"fhwa","url":"https://www.fhwa.dot.gov/byways","retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"},{"name":"OpenStreetMap contributors (ODbL)","src":"osm","url":"https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright","retrievedAt":"2026-07-10T18:35:17.820Z"}],"endpoints":{"from":"West Union, SC","to":"Gaffney, SC","via":["Cleveland, SC","Gowensville, SC","New Prospect, SC"]},"itinerary":[{"seq":1,"place":"West Union","state":"SC","kind":"terminus","mileFromStart":19.6,"toNextMi":19.2,"note":"The drive begins here","control":["Walhalla","Highlands","Cashiers","Seneca"],"lat":34.75773,"lng":-83.04502,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":2,"place":"Keowee-Toxaway State Park","state":"SC","kind":"park-entrance","mileFromStart":38.8,"toNextMi":25,"note":"Junction toward Six Mile & Clemson","control":["Six Mile","Clemson","Mile Creek County Park"],"lat":34.93173,"lng":-82.88474,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":3,"place":"Cleveland","state":"SC","kind":"town","mileFromStart":63.8,"toNextMi":4.3,"note":"Junction toward Marietta & Travelers Rest","control":["Marietta","Travelers Rest"],"lat":35.0724,"lng":-82.52717,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":4,"place":"Lima","state":"SC","kind":"town","mileFromStart":68.1,"toNextMi":14.1,"note":"Junction toward Greenville & Hendersonville","control":["Greenville","Hendersonville"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":5,"place":"Gowensville","state":"SC","kind":"town","mileFromStart":82.2,"toNextMi":4.1,"note":"Junction toward Landrum & Greer","control":["Landrum","Greer","North Greenville University"],"lat":35.11479,"lng":-82.22514,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":6,"place":"Campobello","state":"SC","kind":"town","mileFromStart":86.3,"toNextMi":7.2,"note":"Junction toward Landrum & Spartanburg","control":["Landrum","Spartanburg"],"lat":35.12326,"lng":-82.14024,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":7,"place":"New Prospect","state":"SC","kind":"town","mileFromStart":93.5,"toNextMi":12.1,"note":"Junction toward Mill Spring & Spartanburg","control":["Mill Spring","Spartanburg"],"lat":35.13195,"lng":-82.04389,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":8,"place":"Chesnee","state":"SC","kind":"town","mileFromStart":105.6,"toNextMi":2.4,"note":"Junction toward Rutherfordton & Spartanburg","control":["Rutherfordton","Spartanburg"],"lat":35.14869,"lng":-81.86304,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":9,"place":"Cowpens NB","state":"SC","kind":"town","mileFromStart":108,"toNextMi":9.9,"note":"Junction toward Forest City & Cowpens","control":["Forest City","Cowpens"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":10,"place":"Gaffney","state":"SC","kind":"terminus","mileFromStart":117.9,"toNextMi":null,"note":"The drive ends here","control":["Charlotte","Spartanburg","Logan Street (SC 18 Conn.)","Union"],"lat":35.10059,"lng":-81.6761,"src":"wikipedia"}],"history":{"paragraphs":["The current highway was once part of the \"Cherokee Path\" or \"Keowee Path,\" this road was the route used by the Cherokee Indians and the English and French fur traders and stretched from Tennessee to Charleston, South Carolina. This National Scenic Byway winds its way through Upstate South Carolina and passes through some towns, such as Walhalla, Salem, Marietta, Campobello, Chesnee, and Gaffney. Echoes of the area's Cherokee heritage can still be heard in places and river names like Seneca, Savannah, Keowee, Jocassee, Enoree, Toxaway, Tugaloo, Tokena, and Eastatoee.","In the city of Gaffney, east of I-85, SC 11 is known as \"Floyd Baker Boulevard,\" which is a well-known street name in Upstate South Carolina.[citation needed] This section of SC 11 is a vast contrast to the rest of the route. At this point the highway becomes heavily congested and developed. Gaffney is also the biggest town along the route.","South Carolina Highway 112 (SC 112) was a state highway that was established in July 1936 on a path from SC 9 in New Prospect to U.S. Route 221 (US 221) and SC 110 in Chesnee. In 1939, it was decommissioned, with most of its path redesignated as part of SC 11."],"sourceSection":"History","src":"wikipedia"},"highlights":[{"n":"West Union","d":"The drive begins here","q":"West Union","lat":34.755,"lng":-83.04111111,"src":"wikipedia"},{"n":"Keowee-Toxaway State Park","d":"Junction toward Six Mile & Clemson","q":"Keowee-Toxaway State Park","lat":34.93,"lng":-82.88305556,"src":"wikipedia"},{"n":"Gaffney","d":"The drive ends here","q":"Gaffney","lat":35.07361111,"lng":-81.62444444,"src":"wikipedia"}],"references":[{"n":1,"text":"\"Highway Logmile Report\". South Carolina Department of Transportation. Retrieved December 3, 2020.","url":"https://ris.scdot.org/LogMileReport.aspx?county=37&type=4&number=11&auxiliary=0&map=y"},{"n":2,"text":"\"Highway Logmile Report\". South Carolina Department of Transportation. Retrieved December 3, 2020.","url":"https://ris.scdot.org/LogMileReport.aspx?county=39&type=4&number=11&auxiliary=0&map=y"},{"n":3,"text":"\"Highway Logmile Report\". South Carolina Department of Transportation. Retrieved December 3, 2020.","url":"https://ris.scdot.org/LogMileReport.aspx?county=23&type=4&number=11&auxiliary=0&map=y"},{"n":4,"text":"\"Highway Logmile Report\". South Carolina Department of Transportation